<DOC><DOCNO> AP880706-0097 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-06-88 0900EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Thailand-Vietnam     07-06 0186</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Thailand-Vietnam,0191</SECOND><HEAD>Seven Thai Villagers Killed in Cambodia Fighting</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Seven people, five of them children,were killed and seven wounded when three artillery shells firedfrom inside Cambodia landed in their village today, an army officersaid.   It was not known who fired the shells into Sai Tho Kao villageof Buriram province near the Cambodian border. Fighting insideCambodia between the Vietnamese-backed government and a coalitionof guerrillas frequently spills into Thailand.   The officer said Thai intelligence had recently received reportsof fighting between Vietnamese troops and Khmer Rouge guerrillasnear the village.   The officer said Thai gunners fired warning shots into Cambodiaafter the shells landed in the village. He spoke on condition henot be identified.   Vietnam says it is withdrawing about 50,000 of its troops fromCambodia, which it invaded in 1978 to rout the Khmer Rouge frompower. The Chinese-backed Khmer Rouge now makes up part of theguerrilla coalition headed by Prince Norondom Sihanouk.   U.S. intelligence reports say Vietnam has already handed overmuch of the military operations along the Thai-Cambodian border togovernment troops.</TEXT></DOC>